# Primary goal of the repository
The ultimate goal of this GitHub repository is to stand out for a future interviewer as an experienced "AI/HPC Solution Architect".

# Code style rules
- Use descriptive variable names that reflect their purpose (e.g., `isAuthenticated`, `fetchUserData`).
- Always include type annotations in Python function definitions.
- Follow industry best practices for HPC and AI solutions, including modular design and scalability.

# Documentation
- Ensure all functions and classes have detailed docstrings explaining their purpose and usage.
- Generate automated documentation for all public APIs.

# Testing
- Write unit tests for all critical components.
- Use pytest for Python projects with at least 90% code coverage.

# Additional best practices
- Optimize code for parallel processing where applicable.
- Include examples of AI/HPC use cases in the README file.